=== Longitudinal Exercise Proteomics

Germain, Hanson, and colleagues (2025) demonstrated that the _pattern_ of proteomic response to exercise---particularly persistent immune/metabolic/neuromuscular dysregulation during the recovery phase---distinguishes ME/CFS from sedentary controls The proteomic signature of PEM (suppressed T/B cell signaling, upregulated glycolysis, disrupted IL-17) captured at 24h post-exercise may serve as an objective PEM biomarker, which is critically needed for clinical trials.


